{
  "texts": [
    "Therefore, defining the DNA damage response (DDR) effector pathways that respond to TMZinduced DNA lesions may reveal new vulnerabilities and opportunities for GBM therapy.",
    "All GBM eventually become TMZ-refractory and recur 22.",
    "It is suggested that therapy-induced mutations account for the adaptations that allow GBM to resist TMZ.",
    "Hypermutation (i.e., a high mutation burden) is rare in newly-diagnosed gliomas, but has been described in recurrent tumors from TMZ-treated patients [23] [24] [25].",
    "The extent to which TMZ-induced hypermutation causes GBM recurrence is still debated 25."
  ]
}